<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-248-366  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 248 366.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  May 1 1989 v28 n9 p50(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Integrated environment eases development of military systems.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Williams, Tom.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Sabtech Industries Inc, LSI Logic Corp, Grid Systems Corp, andReady Systems combined integrated hardware and softwaredevelopment tools to create a complete environment for developing,characterizing and debugging MIL-STD-1750A computer systems.andP;  Thisintegrated environment is organized around the Orbiter 1750Acoprocessor board from Sabtech, which is assigned by the Air Forcefor use in real-time embedded systems for avionics and control ofair and spaceborne systems.andP;  The LSI Logic chip set isparticularly appropriate for use on the Orbiter 1750A coprocessorboard because of the integration of the memory management unit(MMU), and block protect unit in one chip.andP;  These four companiesalso revealed that in addition to this integrated system, abundled system based on the Grid computer will soon be available.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sabtech Industries Inc. (contracts)LSI Logic Corp. (contracts)Grid Systems Corp. (contracts)Ready Systems (contracts).andO;Topic:     TechnologyIntegrated SystemsMilitaryCoprocessorsInstruction SetsProgram Development ToolsProduct DevelopmentSpecificationsArchitecture.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   The RTAda environment. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>